In[16]:
def run_models(train, pred_len=192, input_size=48, freq='15min'):
    model_list = [
      NHITS(h=pred_len, input_size=input_size, scaler_type="robust"),
      RNN(h=pred_len, input_size=input_size, scaler_type="robust"),
      LSTM(h=pred_len, input_size=input_size, scaler_type="robust"),
      BiTCN(h=pred_len, input_size=input_size, scaler_type="robust"),
      KAN(h=pred_len, input_size=input_size, scaler_type="robust"),
    ]

    nf = NeuralForecast(models=model_list, freq=freq)
    nf.fit(df=train)
    forecasts = nf.predict()
    return forecasts

def models_ped_plot(true_value, model, name):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 3))

    true_value.plot(ax=ax, label='True values', title=f'Model {name} predicts', color='#3AE48C')
    model.plot(ax=ax, label=f'{name} model', color='red')
    ax.legend(['True values', f'{name} model'])
    plt.grid(False)
    plt.show()
In[291]:
def calculate_metrics(y_val, forecasts, p=48):
    y_true = y_val.sort_index()
    preds = forecasts.set_index('ds')[['NHITS', 'RNN', 'LSTM', 'BiTCN', 'KAN']]
    preds = preds.loc[y_true.index]

    results = []
    for name in ['NHITS', 'RNN', 'LSTM', 'BiTCN', 'KAN']:
        y_pred = preds[name]
        rmse = np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_true, y_pred))
        mae  = mean_absolute_error(y_true, y_pred)
        mape = np.mean(np.abs((y_true - y_pred) / y_true)) * 100

        results.append((f'{name} {p}', rmse, mae, mape))

    df = pd.DataFrame(results, columns=['model', 'rmse', 'mae', 'mape']).set_index('model')
    return df

from prophet import Prophet
def build_model(train, val, holiday=False, season=False, s_name=None, p=96, calculate_metrics=True, pred_len=None, freq=None):
    model = Prophet()
    if holiday == True:
        model.add_country_holidays(country_name='US')
    if season == True:
        model.add_seasonality(name=s_name, period=p, fourier_order=20)


    if calculate_metrics == False:
        df = pd.concat([train, val], axis=0)
        model.fit(df)
        future_year = model.make_future_dataframe(periods=pred_len, freq=freq)
        forecast = model.predict(future_year)
        return model, forecast
    else:
        model.fit(train)
        future_test = val[['ds']].copy()
        forecast_test = model.predict(future_test)

        y_true = val['y'].values
        y_pred = forecast_test['yhat'].values
        mae = mean_absolute_error(y_true, y_pred)
        rmse = np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_true, y_pred))
        mape = np.mean(np.abs((y_true - y_pred) / y_true)) * 100

        print(f" MAE = {mae:.2f},\n RMSE = { rmse:.2f},\n MAPE = {mape:.2f}")
        if season == True:
            model_name = '_seasonal'
        elif holiday == True:
            model_name = '_holiday'
        else:
            model_name = ' '

        df = pd.DataFrame({'model': [f'Prophet{model_name} {p}'],
                           'rmse':  [rmse],
                           'mae':   [mae],
                           'mape':  [mape],
                          }).set_index('model')

        return forecast_test['yhat'], df



def pred_plot(ds, y_true, y_pred, title=None):
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 6))
    plt.plot(ds, y_true, label='True values', color='black', alpha=0.6)
    plt.plot(ds, y_pred, label='Pred values', color='red', alpha=0.6)
    plt.title(title)
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()

def visualize_split(df, data, title):
    train = df.loc[df.index < data]
    val = df.loc[df.index >= data]

    fig, (ax_seasonal_48, ax_seasonal_96, ax_seasonal_672, ax_seasonal_2976, ax_trend, ax_resid) = plt.subplots(
    6, 1, figsize=(12, 8), sharex=True
)
    fig.suptitle(title)

    train['seasonal 48'].plot(ax=ax_seasonal_48, label='Training Set seasonal 48', color='#3A92E4')
    ax_seasonal_48.axvline(data, color='black', ls='--')
    ax_seasonal_48.set_ylabel("seasonal 48", rotation=30)
    val['seasonal 48'].plot(ax=ax_seasonal_48, label='Val Set seasonal 48', color='#3AE48C')

    train['seasonal 96'].plot(ax=ax_seasonal_96, label='Training Set seasonal 96', color='#3A92E4')
    ax_seasonal_96.axvline(data, color='black', ls='--')
    ax_seasonal_96.set_ylabel("seasonal 96", rotation=30)
    val['seasonal 96'].plot(ax=ax_seasonal_96, label='Val Set seasonal 96', color='#3AE48C')

    train['seasonal 672'].plot(ax=ax_seasonal_672, label='Training Set seasonal 672', color='#3A92E4')
    ax_seasonal_672.axvline(data, color='black', ls='--')
    ax_seasonal_672.set_ylabel("seasonal 672", rotation=30)
    val['seasonal 672'].plot(ax=ax_seasonal_672, label='Val Set seasonal 672', color='#3AE48C')

    train['seasonal 2976'].plot(ax=ax_seasonal_2976, label='Training Set seasonal 2976', color='#3A92E4')
    ax_seasonal_2976.axvline(data, color='black', ls='--')
    ax_seasonal_2976.set_ylabel("seasonal 2976", rotation=30)
    val['seasonal 2976'].plot(ax=ax_seasonal_2976, label='Val Set seasonal 2976', color='#3AE48C')

    train['trend'].plot(ax=ax_trend, label='Training Set trend', color='#3A92E4')
    ax_trend.axvline(data, color='black', ls='--')
    ax_trend.set_ylabel("trend", rotation=30)
    val['trend'].plot(ax=ax_trend, label='Val Set trend', color='#3AE48C')

    train['resid'].plot(ax=ax_resid, label='Training Set resid', color='#3A92E4')
    ax_resid.axvline(data, color='black', ls='--')
    ax_resid.set_ylabel("resid", rotation=30)
    val['resid'].plot(ax=ax_resid, label='Val Set resid', color='#3AE48C')

    plt.show()
    return train, val

from statsmodels.tsa.seasonal import MSTL

stl = MSTL(energy['Value, kWh'], periods=[48, 96, 672, 2976])
res_stl = stl.fit()

decomposed_df = energy.copy()
decomposed_df['trend'] = res_stl.trend
decomposed_df['seasonal 48'] = res_stl.seasonal['seasonal_48']
decomposed_df['seasonal 96'] = res_stl.seasonal['seasonal_96']
decomposed_df['seasonal 672'] = res_stl.seasonal['seasonal_672']
decomposed_df['seasonal 2976'] = res_stl.seasonal['seasonal_2976']
decomposed_df['resid'] = res_stl.resid
decomposed_df['y_adjusted'] = decomposed_df['trend'] + decomposed_df['resid']

print("STL decomposition complete.")

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def prep(df):
    d = df.copy()
    d["ds"] = pd.to_datetime(d["ds"])
    return d.sort_values("ds")

cls = prep(in_class)
home = prep(in_home)

plt.style.use("dark_background")
fig, (ax_cls, ax_home) = plt.subplots(
    2, 1, figsize=(12, 7), sharex=True
)

# --- CLASS ---
ax_cls.set_title("Class (KAN)")
ax_cls.plot(cls["ds"], cls["Forecast"], label="Forecast")
ax_cls.fill_between(cls["ds"], cls["Lower_95"], cls["Upper_95"], alpha=0.20, label="95% interval")
ax_cls.set_ylabel("kWh")
ax_cls.grid(True, alpha=0.2)
ax_cls.legend(loc="upper right")

# --- HOME ---
ax_home.set_title("Home (RNN)")
ax_home.plot(home["ds"], home["Forecast"], label="Forecast")
ax_home.fill_between(home["ds"], home["Lower_95"], home["Upper_95"], alpha=0.20, label="95% interval")
ax_home.set_ylabel("kWh")
ax_home.set_xlabel("Time")
ax_home.grid(True, alpha=0.2)
ax_home.legend(loc="upper right")

ax_home.tick_params(axis="x", labelrotation=30)

fig.suptitle("Class vs Home", y=0.98)
fig.tight_layout(rect=[0, 0, 1, 0.96])
plt.show()
